                <p><strong>Project period:</strong> May 29 - September 30, 2018 (completed)</p>

                <p><strong>Project Budget:</strong> (100% Employment)</p>

                <p><strong>Project partners:</strong> Adana Chamber of Industry (ADASO), International Labor Organization (ILO)</p>

                <p>
                    <strong>Project Summary:</strong> “Project to Improve Participation of Syrians under Temporary Protection and Host Communities in the Labor Market” by the International Labor Organization in Istanbul, Bursa, Gaziantep, Şanlıurfa, Adana, Mersin,  It also covers the provinces of Hatay and Ankara.
                    An application was submitted by the Adana Chamber of Industry and a project was implemented to integrate Syrians living in Adana into the recruitment process between May 29 - September 30, 2018.
                    Within the scope of the project implemented in cooperation with the MEKSA Foundation, five vocational training courses and two Turkish language courses were organized.
                    <br>
                    Object-oriented computer programming course
                    <br>
                    A course in foreign trade
                    <br>
                    A course in general arc electric welding
                    <br>
                    A course in gas welding
                    <br>
                    A course in water-based building paint
                    <br>
                    Turkish language course A1 (2 courses)
